    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="602"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6308: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received February 6—5:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[From Harris:]</p>
                <p>5. [“] January 30, 10 a.m. In Irkutsk Czechs have delivered both Kolchak and the
                    gold to the Bolshevik. The attitude of General Janin in this matter is not yet
                    clear but he appears to have acted contrary to instructions given by the High
                    Commissioners.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>Harris</item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
